Author: ijustneededaname
Text: You should write travel guides, you just inspired me to go do some fun things in my hometown :)

Author: lIdlV
Text: Go out to lands end/sutros baths in the early morning when there’s fog, it’s a magical hike. Hear the fog horn and the waves, imagine all the ships wrecked and walk the labyrinth. Continue down to baker beach, dip your toes in the frigid waters, get a good snap of the golden gate (be aware that the east end is the nude beach). Or Hit up city lights bookstore (read some brautigan), climb up to coit tower, hear the wild parrots, look at the WPA murals. Or go out to angel island. So many opportunities to burn calories you can afford to eat some of the good food.
